My movie theater of choice is shutting back down
Oh well.  I have their subscription service (and I paid for it in full before the pandemic started), so going to see a movie costs me nothing but time and gas money, lol
Regal Cinemas, one of their brands :p
But as you can see, I still haven't gone back.  Shame, Tenet looked interesting, but not even a free large popcorn / soda for my belated birthday could drag me back.
On the bright side, that means my subscription will be extended (again) by however long they stay closed.  Or the theater dies permanently and I just sub to streaming services :/
Theaters and the like are being hit very hard by the pandemic,
Not unsurprising.  Honestly, theaters have been shafted hard by the movie studios.
The way ticket sales are split would kill movie theaters eventually.  They've had to get creative to stay afloat.
More and more people are staying home from theaters thanks to the rise of streaming platforms, ever improving projects / television screens, home audio, etc.
If you've ever complained about how expensive concessions are at the theaters, that's literally how they make most of their money.
